OL,3,CWhy councils in Wales are increasing
OL,4,Ctax and cutting services
OL,6,FShe said: "We've always prioritised
OL,7,Four most vulnerable - so that's social
OL,8,Fcare and education. When we got to the
OL,9,Frealisation, that if we funded all the
OL,10,Fcost pressures for education... it
OL,11,Fwould virtually wipe out our
OL,12,Fneighbourhood services budget.
OL,14,F"So when you've got people saying
OL,15,F'you've got to fill more pot holes or
OL,16,Fwe want you to do x, y and z' in their
OL,17,Fcommunities, how do you weigh that up
OL,18,Fagainst the needs of a young person
OL,19,Fwith autism? Those are the real
OL,20,Fdifficult decisions we find ourselves
OL,21,Fin."
